Thirteen suspected illegal bunkerers have been reportedly arrested by security operatives in Bayelsa and Delta states. The security operatives also recovered three pumping machines and a hose from the suspects just as they destroyed some illegally refined products at the scene. Two leaders of the illegal refinery, simply identified as Inimo Matthew and Suoyo, are said to be on the run. The suspects were arrested during a raid at Ikienghenbiri Community and parts of Obotebe in Bayelsa and Delta by a combined team of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps,NSCDC, Marine Police, soldiers and some officials of the Nigeria Petroleum Development Company, NPDC. It was learnt that two other suspects are in the custody of the Bayelsa Command of the NSCDC, including other seized bunkering items.